<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:27:21 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>拉里·芬克预测算力期货市场的诞生</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/larry-fink-predicts-birth-of-futures-market-for-computing-power</link><description>贝莱德公司首席执行官拉里·芬克表示，全球对计算能力的需求如此巨大，以至于交易者有一天能够在期货市场上押注。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/larry-fink-predicts-birth-of-futures-market-for-computing-power2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:27:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/larry-fink-predicts-birth-of-futures-market-for-computing-power</guid></item><item><title>小鼠的大脑奖励回路被下一代减肥药物抑制</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-brain-reward-circuit-inhibited-by-next-generation-weight-loss-drugs-in-mice</link><description>使用人源化小鼠模型的新研究最终揭开了这些小分子药物在大脑中如何发挥作用的帷幕，揭示了它们不仅告诉身体它已经饱了，而且实际上改变了我们感知“治疗”的方式。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-brain-reward-circuit-inhibited-by-next-generation-weight-loss-drugs-in-mice.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:12:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-brain-reward-circuit-inhibited-by-next-generation-weight-loss-drugs-in-mice</guid></item><item><title>纳米技术驱动的神经退行性疾病治疗创新：重点关注阿尔茨海默病和帕金森病</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nanotechnology-driven-therapeutic-innovations-in-neurodegenerative-disorders-a-focus-on-alzheimers-and-parkinsons-disease</link><description>神经退行性疾病导致大脑和周围组织中神经元的逐渐丧失，同时蛋白质的聚集表现出物理化学性质的改变。这些病症的关键是中枢神经系统的逐渐退化，表现为活动能力受损、行为异常和认知缺陷。蛋白毒性应激、神经炎症、氧化应激和程序性细胞死亡等机制会导致神经元持续功能障碍和死亡。目前，神经退行性疾病缺乏明确的治疗方法，可用的疗法主要提供姑息治疗。纳米技术与医疗实践的结合显着增强了治疗效果和诊断能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nanotechnology-driven-therapeutic-innovations-in-neurodegenerative-disorders-a-focus-on-alzheimers-and-parkinsons-disease.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 12:57:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nanotechnology-driven-therapeutic-innovations-in-neurodegenerative-disorders-a-focus-on-alzheimers-and-parkinsons-disease</guid></item><item><title>研究人员在无意识的人脑中发现高级语言处理</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/researchers-discover-advanced-language-processing-in-the-unconscious-human-brain</link><description>贝勒医学院的研究人员发现，人脑在全身麻醉的无意识状态下能够进行复杂的语言处理。该研究结果发表在最新一期的《自然》杂志上，挑战了我们对意识和认知作用的认知，并可能开辟理解记忆、语言和脑机接口的新方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/researchers-discover-advanced-language-processing-in-the-unconscious-human-brain.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 12:42:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/researchers-discover-advanced-language-processing-in-the-unconscious-human-brain</guid></item><item><title>冠状病毒进入人体细胞的新途径</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-way-coronaviruses-can-get-into-human-cells</link><description>CcCoV-KY43 存在于心鼻蝙蝠（Cardioderma cor）中，这是一种重要的生态物种，主要发现于东非，包括苏丹东部和坦桑尼亚北部。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-new-way-coronaviruses-can-get-into-human-cells2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 12:27:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-way-coronaviruses-can-get-into-human-cells</guid></item><item><title>阿米芬吡啶治疗重症肌无力的疗效和安全性随机、双盲、安慰剂对照交叉试验</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/efficacy-and-safety-of-amifampridine-in-myasthenia-gravisa-randomized-double-blind-placebo-controlled-crossover-trial</link><description>I 类证据表明，在 AChRAb+ 重症肌无力患者中，吡斯的明加用氨苯吡啶并不优于单独使用吡斯的明治疗，并且与较高的不良事件发生率相关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/efficacy-and-safety-of-amifampridine-in-myasthenia-gravisa-randomized-double-blind-placebo-controlled-crossover-trial2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 12:12:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/efficacy-and-safety-of-amifampridine-in-myasthenia-gravisa-randomized-double-blind-placebo-controlled-crossover-trial</guid></item><item><title>NeuroImage 教学：两位终生好友的双侧后肢内囊 T2 高信号和严重小脑萎缩</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/teaching-neuroimage-bilateral-posterior-limb-internal-capsule-t2-hyperintensity-and-severe-cerebellar-atrophy-in-2-lifelong-friends</link><description>该网站使用安全服务来防范恶意机器人。当网站验证您不是机器人时会显示此页面。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/teaching-neuroimage-bilateral-posterior-limb-internal-capsule-t2-hyperintensity-and-severe-cerebellar-atrophy-in-2-lifelong-friends.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 11:57:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/teaching-neuroimage-bilateral-posterior-limb-internal-capsule-t2-hyperintensity-and-severe-cerebellar-atrophy-in-2-lifelong-friends</guid></item><item><title>癌症的遗传缺陷使细胞变成“规则破坏者”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-genetic-defect-in-cancer-that-turns-cells-into-rule-breakers</link><description>科学家利用艾伦研究所的细胞系来了解遗传缺陷如何在干细胞中传播&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-genetic-defect-in-cancer-that-turns-cells-into-rule-breakers2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 11:42:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-genetic-defect-in-cancer-that-turns-cells-into-rule-breakers</guid></item><item><title>潘多拉系外行星任务的第一张图像</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/first-images-from-the-pandora-exoplanet-mission</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 11:27:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/first-images-from-the-pandora-exoplanet-mission</guid></item><item><title>细胞和亚细胞专业化使生物学限制的深度学习成为可能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cellular-and-subcellular-specialization-enables-biology-constrained-deep-learning</link><description>加洛尼等人。介绍“树突目标传播”：一种符合戴尔定律的皮质微电路学习算法，具有体细胞和树突目标抑制和现实的连接约束。通过结合实验得出的 BTSP 和 Hebbian 规则，树突通过 E/I 不匹配计算局部错误代理，在同时自下而上和自上而下的信号传输过程中支持基于梯度的深度学习。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cellular-and-subcellular-specialization-enables-biology-constrained-deep-learning2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 11:12:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cellular-and-subcellular-specialization-enables-biology-constrained-deep-learning</guid></item></channel></rss>